File: compiler/js-generic-lowering.cc
Relevant lowerings:
- void JSGenericLowering::LowerJSCreateWithContext(Node* node) { ScopeInfoRef scope_info = ScopeInfoOf(node->op()); node->InsertInput(zone(), 1, jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(scope_info, broker())); ReplaceWithRuntimeCall(node, Runtime::kPushWithContext); }
- void JSGenericLowering::LowerJSCreateCatchContext(Node* node) { ... ReplaceWithRuntimeCall(node, Runtime::kPushCatchContext); }
- void JSGenericLowering::LowerJSCreateBlockContext(Node* node) { ... ReplaceWithRuntimeCall(node, Runtime::kPushBlockContext); }
- REPLACE_STUB_CALL(ToObject) expands to LowerJSToObject(Node*): ReplaceWithBuiltinCall(node, Builtin::kToObject).
- JSLoadContext/JSStoreContext/JSHasContextExtension/JSLoadScriptContext/JSStoreScriptContext: UNREACHABLE in generic lowering (eliminated in typed/context specialization), indicating TF specializes context access before generic lowering.
- Load/Store global and property lowerings use IC/builtins; unrelated but confirms fast-paths for global lookups are via ICs not generic runtime.
- JSCallRuntime handling: LowerJSCallRuntime dispatches to runtime calls (used for LoadLookupSlot/StoreLookupSlot when emitted by BGB as JSCallRuntime).
